5	Warranty Terms	The goods we sell are new, tested and packaged by the producer. The detectors and the coils are supplied with a warranty card and user guide. The warranty term for is as follows:\n- 5 years for the main electronic board of the detectors\n- 2 years for the rest - battery charger, search coil, headphones, keypad, potentiometers and shafts\n\nWhen the final purchaser/user is a company, the warranty term is 2 years from the date of the purchase.\n\nThe warranty does NOT cover any physical damage, caused by the user, no matter if by accident or intentionally, that could be avoided by normal careful usage - broken or damaged parts, cables, knobs and cable plugs. The warranty does NOT cover batteries.\n\nPlease do not open the device or try to repair it yourself or by any other unauthorized person. Such actions lead to warranty void. Warranty repairs shall be made ONLY by the producer.\n\nIn case of warranty claim, prior of taking any other action, please contact us by e-mail with detailed description of the problem occurring with your product and we will get back to you ASAP with detailed instructions on how to proceed.\n\nProducts under warranty that need repair or replacement, must be returned to our office address at your cost. If the repair is under the warranty conditions, we will pay the shipping charge from our address to yours, otherwise (if the damage is caused by the user), you will have to pay the shipping charge for the return shipping. The return shipment shall be made from the name of the original purchaser and from the country the detector was initially shipped to.\n\nIf you reside outside the EU, it may be impossible to return a product for repair because of customs clearance issues. Please contact us before shipping a detector for repair! Otherwise the customs may reject the import and your parcel may be returned.	2024-12-11 02:34:10.01+00
6	Returns	The goods must be returned at your own cost, in their original packaging, within 14 days from the receipt date, in the same condition they were originally received. We will refund the full amount paid (less the shipping charge and the PayPal fee, if the payment is made through PayPal) for the goods as long as they are returned suitably packaged and in unused condition with their original packaging. If the goods have any mark of usage or missing parts from the original set, they will be deemed as accepted by the purchaser, no refund is applicable, we will reship the goods to you.\n\nPlease contact us before proceeding to a return and let us know the reason. We will investigate the problem and will give you instructions on how to proceed with the return. Refunds will be made within 14 days after we receive the returned goods.\n\nCustomer Complaints Handling\nIf a product that has been purchased from GoldenMaskDetectors.com does not match your expectations or you have a dissatisfaction of any kind regarding the shop or the goods offered, please contact us by e-mail and let us know the details and the nature of your complaint. Please describe the problem as detailed as possible. We will handle your complaint ASAP (usually within 7 working days) and will let you know what initial action we will take to resolve the problem, if any. We will keep you informed by email of the progress we are making with your dispute.\n\nReturned non-delivered parcels\nParcels are returned by the shipping companies if they are unable to deliver the parcel within two delivery attempts. Reasons for this could be: you provided a wrong address and/or phone number; you are not at the address you provided; you refuse to receive the parcel; you refuse to pay the import duties (if any).\n\nWe do always ship to the address you provide with the order, so if the parcel cannot be delivered, this is most probably your fault. If the parcel is returned from a EU country, we will refund you the full order value minus the shipping charge. If the return is from a non-EU country, it could be a loss for you. In this case we will refund the order value minus the shipping charge and minus all the following expenses we will have to pay - the return shipping charge; parcel storage tax in your country (if any); import/export papers handling taxes (if any); import duties in Bulgaria (when the parcel is imported back) and import procedure tax in our country. In this case, a refund could take up to 3 months	2024-12-11 02:34:10.863+00
7	Privacy Policy (GDPR)	Personal Data Protection Policy\nGMD does not collect any personal information about you except for information that you voluntarily provide when you submit an email or an order for a product that we sell through this shop. All the personal information is treated confidentially and is carefully protected from unauthorized use. As a personal information we consider the following: your name, postal address, IP address (location), e-mail address, bank account number and phone number.\n\nWe do not use user profiles with our store, so all personal information about our customers is stored on the PayPal servers and you can manage the stored information from your PayPal account. We use the information from PayPal to issue an invoice for your order and to ship the order to your address. We keep some of your personal data only for accounting purposes, according to the Bulgarian tax and accounting law and in accordance with the EU GDPR act.\n\nWe do not collect, nor we could see any credit/debit card information - those are accessed only by our card processing partner - PayPal.\n\nCookies\nWhat are cookies?\nA cookie is a small text file that a website saves on your computer or mobile device when you visit the site. It enables the website to remember your actions and preferences (such as login, language, font size and other display preferences) over a period of time, so you don’t have to keep re-entering them whenever you come back to the site or browse from one page to another.\n\nHow do we use cookies?\nOur website uses two cookies - one to store your shipping destination choice and a second one to store the cookie consent status. The first cookie named "gmd_stored_country" expires in 30 days, the second one, named "cookieconsent_status" expires after 365 days .\n\nWe use Google Analytics to monitor the performance of our website and Google needs to use cookies for it's system to function properly. Please consult the Google Analytics website for more information about how Google uses cookies.\nWe use Facebook Pixel to manage our Facebook advertising campaigns. Facebook sets cookies on your computer to better point our adverts. Please consult the Facebook website for more information about how Facebook uses cookies.\n\nCookies may be used by the payment gateways we use to process payments.\n\nHow to control cookies\nYou can control and/or delete cookies as you wish – for details, see aboutcookies.org. You can delete all cookies that are already on your computer and you can set most browsers to prevent them from being placed. If you do this, however, you may have to manually adjust some preferences every time you visit a site and some services and functionalities may not work.	2024-12-11 02:34:11.646+00
